reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice, inexpensive addition to our silverware.
reviews.reviewText: I was drawn to this set of silverware because they had a tray that came with it, to use in the drawer, and they looked very similar to my current set of silverware. The tray is very nice, but unfortunately was too big to fit in my drawer, so I use it elsewhere in the house. The silverware is a nice weight and comfortable, but I have noticed that a few of the pieces have either been dinged or sat in water too long and have begun to show small rust spots.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewText: As a second set, this met our expectation and arrived safely.It was however packaged poorly and luckily not to be damaged. The white tape used to seal box did not stick to the cardboard. One side completely broken away and a piece of white internal foam was on my doorstep. The tape on other side had not stuck. The loose cutlery peppered the inside lid with pot marks.As I said very lucky nothing was damaged

reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Fine for Short Term Use
reviews.reviewText: These utensils look fine upon delivery and will get one by, but they are light weight and rust easily. They are inexpensive and there's usually a trade off. If you need a set to get you by for a year or so this is a great purchase, but don't expect beyond that and DO dry them off after washing to keep rusting at bay!
